caption: Went here for a Sunday meal with a friend. Great beer selection. The Buffalo cauliflower was not breaded which was surprising. I got a pastrami sandwich which was very good and made great leftovers for lunch the next day. Over all good, but not fantastic.

Pho Joint is a pop up within Duke's grocery. From my experience this past week I sure hope it catches on. On a mild winter day I sat outside lunch time , the only diner. Pho ga, the chicken version, had the hoped-for rich fragrance along with bite size pieces of dark and light meat chicken, 2 kinds of rice noodles and the standard accompaniments - basil, bean sprouts, lime instead of lemon, a hot sauce and an especially tasty plum sauce. $12 for a big steaming bowl of yummy comfort.
What a cool place. Great beer, reasonable priced pickles...😉
Best burger in dc

Great atmosphere and great food! Servers were super helpful and they really accommodated us throughout our experience, especially with a baby on hand.  Food and drinks took maybe 10-15 minutes to come out so the wait time was astonishingly low!  Taking off one star because the register system couldn't split the check by item, so we had to split the receipt in half. Kinda nit-picky but that was kinda weird.  Other than that this is a must visit restaurant in DC!
Stumbled upon this delicious place! Kinda family friendly! Amazing food!
Their burgers are to die for, and happy hour from 12-7. Would highly recommend
They are rude nobody wants to help you to get a table they will ignore you because I don’t think they like what they do! 👎🏻🤔

Duke’s Grocery is a cozy restaurant within the 2001 Penn complex.  They also have outside dining although the seats are limited.   During my visit Duke’s was offering a comfort menu.  I ordered the Shepherd’s Pie which arrived within its cookware.  The seasoning was just right and had a nice mixture of lamb with potatoes.  The restaurant manager was a very affable and welcoming person.  However, his server acted like she did not want to be there.  Overall, a nice place to grab an informal lunch.
Excellent food! Also, Aton is simply the best!
Duke’s becoming my regular stop when I visit DC , one of my favorite burgers

(Translated by Google) Excellent burger and atmosphere but to pay $ 18 you should at least come with fries.  (Original) Excelente hamburguesa y ambiente pero para pagar 18 dólares por lo menos debería venir con papas fritas.
Great food great service great people
tried the impossible burger it was very nice
Great food and service!

A constantly varying menu with special-trip worthy mainstays. Possibly the best burger in DC. Fresh ingredients throughout. Consistently delicious. Great drinks. Awesome staff. I've been going since they opened and have celebrated my birthday here. Love it.

Each item on the menu is thoughtfully crafted. Pancakes, truffle Mac and cheese and the corn appetizers were amazing and so are the burgers of course. Quinoa salad was simple and delicious. This was our 2nd time so we tried a few other items. Customer service is top notch. Anton and his staff are so friendly and professional. Perfect lunch on a gloomy Sunday!
Under cooked my burger fries weren't done
Absolutely be eating here again!
Nice place with nice staff and GREAT food! Tried both the brunchie burger and the Mac'n cheese and they were both amazing! I will go again!
Great wagu burger. So delicious!
Yulia S  is an amazing server she was very attentive. As well the food here is amazing. All the staff was great and helpful.
Fish and chips are great!
Nice place! A bit too warm inside! Great burger (should come with fries) great brisket sandwich!

I have never been speechless eating food before. Their Brunchie Burger is incredible. The atmosphere reminds you of a small English pub. Everything about this place is incredible. I would definitely recommend coming here.
Sat outside, had a great meal and fast, friendly service - well recommended
The food is great.
Great food!  Excellent service!

I had a life changing meal at this restaurant!! The Earth To Sea Tartine: red beet cured salmon/ goat cheese & hemp seed spread/ mint chive infusion/ roasted beet chip/ olive oil/ multigrain. Was amazing 👏 😍 I love beets and now I have found beet Heaven!!
Very fine food and beer.
Best burger in Washington! With lots of other great options on the menu. Excellent service and environment. Truffle mac n cheese is delicious
Great burgers!

Fish and Chips! I wholeheartedly recommend this option. The portion is great and they taste delicious. It’s a pretty basic item but I was pleasantly surprised. I had some disappointing experiences with the burger here so I’m glad I have it another shot with the fish and chips. I recommend this over the burger. The amount of fries is enough to share!
Awesome oasis in the middle of a hot, sticky day in DC. Try the spicy Margarita and baked Mac and cheese 👌

Had never heard of this place and saw that they’ve been rated the best burger in DC, so naturally I had to try one. I have to say that it is definitely a contender! Cooked to perfection and perfectly crafted. Quick and friendly service as well.
A British inspired tavern with nice outdoor patio make Dukes an ideal place to grab a bite to eat.

It was so hot today I couldn't imagine eating anything too robust so I went with the quinoa salad and was not disappointed & I am not generally a salad person. The waiter was awesome & service was on point (esp during covid times)
Delicious, quick service, great drinks
Delicious burger and great service for curbside pick up. So glad they opened this location.

Goood LOOOORRD......its been a while since I have had my eyes coin round, this is the best burger ive ever tried period.... I didnt have many options while working, so I decided to gove this small grocery bussiness a try.  the person I talk to was extremely helpful, the service is superb, very kind, and the food, I ate two proper burgers, GOOD GOD!!!
Great place to grab drinks! Awesome vibe!
Nice ambience and cocktails. Friendly and swift service. Recommend the pork “wings” as an appetizer.
Spectacular understated place! The wait staff were friendly, food was exceptional and  the selection of beers complimented the whole experience. Recommend, recommend, recommend!
A little too loud for dinner conversation, IMHO (at 530p) but great burgers (spicy chicken was excellent) and decent service for a 'college bar'.
Amazing place. I came here to catch up with old friends. The staff, food and ambiance were perfect!

Quick pit stop here in DC and would definitely return. Highly recommend the Avo toast and impossible burger. My boyfriend didn’t believe it wasn’t really meat- it was that good! Quick and efficient service as well. Staff were all lovely.
Great food

Amazing burger and fries! I went on a Saturday during lunch time and didn’t know that they wouldn’t have their regular menu in addition to the brunch menu. I went with the only burger they had, and it was amazing. Great burger for a reasonable price. And some of the best fries I’ve had! Will go again and again.
Such a delicious burger. The price is little expensive than other stores but it worth. Waitress and waiters are so good, too kind. I recommend this store.
Nice atmosphere, good service
Great burger and beer! Service was excellent
Fantastic service, excellent drink selection, and the proper burger is the best you can get in this part of DC.
Really tasty burgers. The sweet red chili sauce is great!!  Everything was made fresh for us and came out hot.
Amazing burger

Duke's Grocery has launched its second location as a popular neighborhood addition to Foggy Bottom's limited selection. Part bar. Part restaurant. One of DC's original Instagrammable burgers. Really good fish and chips. The rest of the menu looked worthy of a return.
Standard burger with fries
Great bar !! Amazing food. Keep up the great work.

Amazing food with great service! I came for the impossible burger because I’ve been hearing the talk that these guys have the best in the city. And it did not disappoint. I usually like my burger very simple, lettuce ketchup mustard pickles but I decided to switch it up a bit and try it as is. I’m glad I did because the various elements like the Gouda cheese mixed with the arugula was spot on. And the crispy fries just brought everything together.  I also wanted a very good non alcoholic drink so my waiter recommended a blend of lemonade, cranberry juice and pineapple juice. The waitor was named Weal and he was very fast and attentive. Overall the experience was great and this will be a go to happy hour spot for me. And a chill alias weekend spot when I wanna get away from the noise.
Great Burger and great service.
Liberty sandwich was terrific, with a crispy baguette and juicy chopped steak.  Reasonable prices.  Definitely worth going to again!

Same as the other Duke's locations, ostensibly, but the newest spot in the chain seems to still be working out some kinks. The food was on point, but the staff pool seems to have drawn heavily from the nearby GW student population and the service seemed a little disaffected and, therefore, ineffective. Probably worth another visit at some point to see if they've ironed everything out, but for now, it's just another downtown option.
Excellent food, friendly service.

As far as the food (impossible burger) and staff, everything was on point from the moment I stepped on in. Bartender was personable and cool and the greeter was real kind. Manager even stopped by to check on things. Went during lunch and was in and out.
Best burger I've ever had.

Enjoyed the Proper Burger, very good favor.

The Proper Burger had been on my Food Bucket List for a long time.  Now that I've had one, I've been told I have to add Duke's Mac and Cheese to the list.   My server, Rasaun, was so nice and helpful even though I just ordered a burger this time.  I'm planning to go back and work my way through the rest of the menu.
SO. GOOD. the pancakes are delicious and you can never go wrong with the burger!
Completely impressed by staff. Great environment. They are not lying about the burger!
Great outdoor seating, good service, lovely bar, and great lunch option neat Foggy Bottom.
Really really good burger. Honest prices. Fast and courteous service. Will come back again!

Disappointed based on high rating. Mediocre beer selection (mostly owned by major labels, does not rotate). Burger was ok but far from best in dc. (Arugula was skimpy, bun fell apart). Tomato salad was meh (added shrimp good, tomatoes were tasteless grape tomatoes). Service was very good. Overall just OK.

English pub theme brunch place. One of my absolute favorites and with locations throughout the city, you can choose the one closest to you! Food is delicious and staff is helpful and wonderful. Full English Breakfast is one of their staples, but their other food is also great to grab with a friend.
One of the best burgers I've had in a long time, and the bacon was incredibly thick and cooked to perfection. Not too soft, not too crunchy. Great smoked flavor
I love the crudo toast.
Service and food

Had the Proper Burger and fries. Waiter had sold me on trying the burger since it had won DC's best burger for the last four years. Burger was excellent. Best one that I have had in years. The fries were okay, but nothing special.
Demetri is the best bartender maybe ever....he made all my cocktails with fresh fruit and knew every drink. Also very friendly, will definitely be make this a continuous spot. He was the best!!!
What do you get when you cross dukes with Applebee’s and locate it in an eastern bloc country that doesn’t know what customer service means? This place.

That truffle mac n cheese is to die for... I ate as much as I could while there and took a sizable portion home.. forgot about it in the fridge.... a week later all warmed up.. geez how could it get even better? Nice ambiance as well.
Best burger in DC!
We weren't sure this was a restaurant at first,  but so glad we decided to eat here,  the food was delicious!  Lots of flavors bursting,  Great combos of flavors!  Food came out very fast!

Dennis is the most wonderful Host and manager. He got us in quickly and served us in person. Where do you get service like this?

Has great happy hour deals. The food is good as well. The burger is apparently the best in DC, it is a bit sweet though. The truffle flavored chips are great. The shrimp sandwich was a little bland and too much bread to shrimp ratio. The location is nice and open space.
